message: To succeed, first use the 'growth serum' on EACH of your initial ingredients (once per ingredient) to get them all to a positive 'grown' state. Next, focus on combining these 'grown' ingredients. The most valuable combinations seem to involve items from different habitats: land, water, and air. Aim to create one complex item that includes features from all three habitats. Once you have this multi-habitat item, apply the 'growth serum' to it ONE time. This often creates a 'super-grown' version with a significant value increase (e.g., from 30-40 to 45-50). However, be warned: applying 'growth serum' a second time to an already 'super-grown' item, or adding too many components (especially redundant habitats), tends to drastically decrease its value. The 'mutation catalyst' has consistently caused value drops in my experience, so it's best to avoid it. Your highest score will likely come from a 'super-grown' item combining 2-3 distinct habitats.

Focus on combining 2-3 'grown' items that share similar habitats (e.g., land + land, air + air, or land + air) to create valuable hybrids. Avoid using 'mutation catalyst' on any item with a positive value, as it almost always turns them negative. It can sometimes reduce the negativity of already negative items, or rarely turn a negative complex item positive, but this is a high-risk gamble. Secure your best positive score by submitting before risking a value drop, especially if you're above 30-40.

message: Here's what I learned: 1. Always apply 'growth serum' to every initial ingredient first. Small items become 5, medium become 10, large become 15. 2. Combining 2-3 'grown' ingredients that live in different environments (land, water, air) is the best way to get high scores (around 40-45). For example, grown land + grown water + grown air. 3. DO NOT combine more than 3 ingredients, as a fourth ingredient consistently leads to an 'overcomplicated' item with negative value. 4. 'Mutation catalyst' is tricky: using it once makes an item value 0 (mutant), but using it a second time on that 0-value item can yield 30 (super-mutant). A third use makes it negative. Stick to growth serum and 2-3 ingredient combines for consistency.

message: The 'growth serum' is your best friend initially; use it once on every starting ingredient to get positive values and the 'grown' feature. Avoid the 'mutation catalyst' as it consistently decreased item value in my experience. The most successful strategy for high scores is combining 'grown' items, especially those from different habitats (e.g., land and water, or land and air). Combining items of similar habitats but different types (e.g., two air creatures) also works well. Once you have a few combined items with values around 20-30, it's generally best to submit, as over-processing or repeated tool use often leads to negative values.
